>> Diabetes UK Northern Ireland works with local politicians, MLAs and the
Assembly structures to campaign for better services for people with diabetes.
>> The Northern Ireland Assembly is the devolved government for Northern
Ireland and is responsible for most of the day-to-day issues affecting the
>> Diabetes UK Northern Ireland works with Ministers, MLAs and Civil Servants
to ensure they are aware of issues relating to diabetes and that these issues
>> This group pulls together interested MLAs so that we can keep them abreast
of developments in the field of diabetes care. The Group members have pledged
to support Diabetes UK in obtaining better services for those with diabetes
and generally meet three to four times a year. The Chair of the All Party
Group is Pat Ramsey MLA, Deputy Chair is Stewart Dickson Cllr, MLA, Secretary
is Thomas Buchanan, MLA and Treasurer is Mickey Brady MLA.
